cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with instance-aware semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new neural network architecture, which involves joint prediction and classification, and achieves state-of-the-art performance. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper mentions that it wins the COCO 2016 segmentation competition, which is a benchmark for object detection and segmentation. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
